content.text:
Here’s a **learn-by-doing** path using **HTML, CSS, and a little JavaScript** in **VS Code**. No React or npm yet — you’ll see how a real site is built from the ground up.

---

## What you’ll build

A **single-page** ramen shop site with:

- Hero (big title + photo feel)
- About
- Menu (cards with prices)
- Hours & location
- Contact footer

You’ll open it in the browser with **Live Server** (a VS Code extension).

---

## Part 0: Tools (5 minutes)

1. Open **VS Code**.
2. Install extension: **Live Server** (by Ritwick Dey).  
   - Extensions icon (left sidebar) → search `Live Server` → Install.
3. Create a folder on your Desktop, e.g. `C:\Users\FUNNY\Desktop\ramen-shop`.
4. In VS Code: **File → Open Folder** → choose `ramen-shop`.

You should have an empty folder in the Explorer (left side).

---

## Part 1: Your first file — `index.html` (structure)

1. In Explorer, click **New File** → name it `index.html`.
2. Paste this skeleton:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Ichiban Ramen</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
</head>
<body>

  <header class="site-header">
    <a class="logo" href="#">Ichiban Ramen</a>
    <nav>
      <a href="#about">About</a>
      <a href="#menu">Menu</a>
      <a href="#visit">Visit</a>
      <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section id="hero" class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Est. 2019 · Your City</p>
      <h1>Slow broth. Fresh noodles.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Tonkotsu simmered 24 hours. Walk-ins welcome before 6pm.</p>
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#menu">View menu</a>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="section">
      <h2>Our story</h2>
      <p>
        We opened with one goal: honest ramen — rich broth, springy noodles,
        and toppings that matter. Every bowl is made to order.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="menu" class="section">
      <h2>Menu</h2>
      <div class="menu-grid">
        <article class="menu-card">
          <h3>Tonkotsu Classic</h3>
          <p>Pork bone broth, chashu, soft egg, nori</p>
          <span class="price">$14.50</span>
        </article>
        <article class="menu-card">
          <h3>Shoyu Chicken</h3>
          <p>Soy-based clear broth, chicken thigh, scallion</p>
          <span class="price">$13.00</span>
        </article>
        <article class="menu-card">
          <h3>Spicy Miso</h3>
          <p>Red miso, ground pork, corn, chili oil</p>
          <span class="price">$15.00</span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="visit" class="section">
      <h2>Visit us</h2>
      <p><strong>Hours</strong><br />Mon–Thu 11am–9pm · Fri–Sat 11am–10pm · Sun 12pm–8pm</p>
      <p><strong>Address</strong><br />123 Noodle Street, Your City</p>
      <a href="https://maps.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open in Google Maps</a>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer id="contact" class="site-footer">
    <p>Call us: <a href="tel:+15551234567">(555) 123-4567</a></p>
    <p>© 2026 Ichiban Ramen</p>
  </footer>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

**What you learned:**

| Piece | Role |
|--------|------|
| `<!DOCTYPE html>` | Tells the browser “this is HTML5” |
| `<head>` | Title, charset, links to CSS |
| `<body>` | Everything visible |
| `<section id="...">` | Blocks you can link to with `#menu` |
| `<link href="styles.css">` | Connects your stylesheet |
| `<script src="script.js">` | Connects JS at the end |

3. Save: **Ctrl + S**.

4. Right-click `index.html` → **Open with Live Server**.  
   Browser opens; it will look plain until Part 2.

---

## Part 2: Make it look good — `styles.css`

1. New file: `styles.css` (same folder as `index.html`).
2. Paste:

```css
/* Reset-ish: consistent box model */
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
  background: #1a1a1a;
  color: #f5f0e8;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

a {
  color: #f0b429;
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

/* Header */
.site-header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 1rem 2rem;
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  background: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.95);
  border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
  z-index: 10;
}

.logo {
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  color: #f5f0e8;
}

.site-header nav a {
  margin-left: 1.5rem;
  color: #ccc;
}

.site-header nav a:hover {
  color: #f0b429;
}

/* Hero */
.hero {
  min-height: 70vh;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 4rem 2rem;
  background: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.6), rgba(0,0,0,0.6)),
    url("https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1569718212165-3a8278f5c1f0?w=1200") center/cover;
}

.eyebrow {
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: #f0b429;
}

.hero h1 {
  font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  margin: 0.5rem 0;
}

.lead {
  max-width: 32rem;
  color: #ccc;
}

/* Buttons */
.btn {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.btn-primary {
  background: #d35400;
  color: #fff;
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background: #e67e22;
  text-decoration: none;
}

/* Sections */
.section {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 4rem 2rem;
}

.section h2 {
  font-size: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  border-bottom: 2px solid #d35400;
  display: inline-block;
  padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
}

/* Menu grid */
.menu-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
}

.menu-card {
  background: #252525;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  border: 1px solid #333;
  transition: transform 0.2s;
}

.menu-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
}

.menu-card h3 {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.price {
  display: block;
  margin-top: 1rem;
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #f0b429;
}

/* Footer */
.site-footer {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 2rem;
  border-top: 1px solid #333;
  color: #888;
}
```

3. Save. Live Server usually **auto-refreshes**; if not, refresh the browser.

**What you learned:**

- **Selectors** (`body`, `.hero`, `#menu`) target elements.
- **Colors** with hex (`#1a1a1a`).
- **Flexbox** in `.hero` and `.site-header` for layout.
- **Grid** in `.menu-grid` for responsive cards.
- **`clamp()`** for responsive font size.

**Try this yourself:** Change `#d35400` to another color and save — see the site update.

---

## Part 3: Small interactivity — `script.js`

1. New file: `script.js`.
2. Paste:

```javascript
// Smooth scroll when clicking nav links (optional polish)
document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach((link) => {
  link.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const id = link.getAttribute("href");
    if (id === "#") return;
    const target = document.querySelector(id);
    if (!target) return;
    e.preventDefault();
    target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth" });
  });
});

// Log when page loads — open DevTools (F12) → Console to see it
console.log("Ichiban Ramen site loaded!");
```

3. Save, refresh browser.
4. Press **F12** → **Console** tab — you should see the message.
5. Click **Menu** in the nav — page should scroll smoothly.

**What you learned:**

- `document.querySelectorAll` finds elements.
- `addEventListener("click", ...)` runs code on click.
- `preventDefault()` stops the jump; `scrollIntoView` animates instead.

---

## Part 4: Folder structure (what you should have)

```text
ramen-shop/
  index.html    ← structure & content
  styles.css    ← look & layout
  script.js     ← behavior
```

That’s the classic **three-file** pattern many small sites use.

---

## Part 5: Customize (your homework)

Do these one at a time; save and check the browser after each:

1. Replace **Ichiban Ramen** with your shop name everywhere.
2. Change menu items and prices in `index.html`.
3. Replace the hero image URL in `styles.css` with another [Unsplash ramen photo](https://unsplash.com/s/photos/ramen).
4. Add a 4th `.menu-card` by copying one `<article>...</article>` block.
5. Change hours and address to real (or fake) info.
6. Add `target="_blank"` only on external links (Maps) — you already did that.

---

## Part 6: VS Code habits that help you learn

| Action | Shortcut (Windows) |
|--------|---------------------|
| Save | Ctrl + S |
| Format document | Shift + Alt + F |
| Split editor (HTML + CSS side by side) | Drag tab to the side |
| Emmet shortcut | Type `section.section` + Tab → expands to HTML |

**Emmet example:** In `index.html`, type `div.menu-grid` and press **Tab** — it expands to `<div class="menu-grid"></div>`.

---

## Part 7: How the browser “reads” your site

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A[index.html] --> B[Loads styles.css]
  A --> C[Loads script.js]
  B --> D[Browser paints layout & colors]
  C --> E[JS runs after HTML exists]
```

Order matters: HTML first, then CSS while parsing, then JS at the bottom so the page exists before your script runs.

---

## Part 8: Next learning steps (when Part 1–7 feel easy)

| Step | What to learn | Why |
|------|----------------|-----|
| 1 | Add a real photo file `images/hero.jpg` and use `url("images/hero.jpg")` | Local assets vs URLs |
| 2 | **Responsive nav** (hamburger menu on mobile) | CSS media queries |
| 3 | **Google Fonts** (Noto Serif JP + Inter) | Typography |
| 4 | **Form** for contact (name, message) | `<form>`, inputs |
| 5 | **Vite + React** | Reusable components when the site grows |

Don’t jump to React until you’re comfortable editing HTML/CSS without feeling lost.

---

## Common problems

| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Page is unstyled | Check `styles.css` is in the same folder; `<link href="styles.css">` spelling |
| Live Server won’t start | Install extension; right-click `index.html`, not the folder |
| Image doesn’t show | URL typo; or use a full `https://` URL like in the example |
| Nav jump is jerky | Make sure `script.js` is linked and saved |
| Changes don’t appear | Save file (Ctrl+S); hard refresh Ctrl+F5 |

---

## Suggested learning schedule

- **Day 1:** Parts 1–2 (HTML + CSS), customize text and colors.  
- **Day 2:** Part 3 (JS), add a 4th menu item, tweak hero.  
- **Day 3:** Add `images/` folder, swap Unsplash for your own image.  
- **Day 4:** Media query — stack header nav on small screens (look up “CSS media query max-width 600px”).  
- **Day 5:** Publish free on [Netlify Drop](https://app.netlify.com/drop) — drag your folder onto the page.

---

## When you want help in Cursor

Stay in **Ask mode** if you want explanations (“why doesn’t my grid work?”).  
Switch to **Agent mode** if you want me to **create the files in your folder** or debug a specific error — paste the error or a screenshot of VS Code.

If you tell me your **shop name** and whether you’re on **Windows** (you are), I can give you the **Day 4 mobile nav** lesson as the next step-by-step chapter only when you’re ready.

